government.geographic_border.definition: A line of demarcation around a geographic space or between one geographic space and another geographic space.

government.government_service.name: Government Service
government.government_service.definition: A named combination of goods, doing-of-work-for-others, and entitlements that can be offered to constituents.

government.health_condition.name: Health Condition
government.health_condition.definition: A state of well-being of a human being or biological organism.

government.human_resource.name: Human Resource
government.human_resource.definition: An individual who has, plans to have, or has had a legal agreement with the organization, which may include compensation and other benefits, on a temporary or permanent basis.

government.incident.name: Incident
government.incident.definition: An unplanned, disruptive or potentially disruptive experience.

government.infrastructure.name: Infrastructure
government.infrastructure.definition: A physical structure or facility, which may include power grids, communication lines, railways, roadways, bridges, tunnels, and pipelines or conduits for water, gas, and power.

government.initiative.name: Initiative
government.initiative.definition: A coordinated collection of temporary endeavors undertaken to create a unique outcome.

government.inquiry.name: Inquiry
government.inquiry.definition: A question, request, feedback, or comment that may exist inside or outside of the organization.

government.intellectual_property_rights.name: Intellectual Property Rights
government.intellectual_property_rights.definition: A legal protection, such as patent, trademark, or copyright.

government.interaction.name: Interaction
government.interaction.definition: A set of contemporaneous collaborations or contacts about a given subject, over a span of time, between two or more entities, using one or more channels, at one or more physical or virtual locations such as meetings, interviews, seminars, or consultations.

government.investment_portfolio.name: Investment Portfolio
government.investment_portfolio.definition: A set of resources expected to increase in value or provide income.

government.job.name: Job
government.job.definition: A named category of accountabilities, whether remunerative or non-remunerative, associated with an assigned, specific, and accountable business duty, role, or function that can be executed by a human or non-human resource.

government.language.name: Language
government.language.definition: A method of communication or dialect variant consisting of units of representation or meaning, such as numbers, words, symbols, sounds, or other physical manifestations and gestures, presented in a structured way.

government.legislation.name: Legislation
government.legislation.definition: A set of authoritative directives that include laws or related statutory instruments.

government.license.name: License
government.license.definition: An authorization to perform a regulated activity, awarded by duly recognized governmental agency or third party, applied to an individual or organization, to engage in an activity, such as fishing, or use of regulated objects, such as modes of transportation or hazardous materials.

government.license_term.name: License Term
government.license_term.definition: A legally enforceable condition set forth within the bounds of a license.

government.market.name: Market
government.market.definition: Individuals, populations of individuals, or organizations constituting the demand for existing or future products and services.

government.material.name: Material
government.material.definition: Food, ingredients, chemicals, waste, and other physical elements used to enable an outcome including sustaining life, the growing of crops, the construction of assets and infrastructure, and the powering of equipment and conveyors.

government.message.name: Message
government.message.definition: A verbal, written, recorded, or digitally-represented communication, including missives, notifications, alerts, and other internally or externally targeted communication about the organization's mission, products, plans, activities, and other focal points.

government.natural_resource.name: Natural Resource
government.natural_resource.definition: Matter that can occur in nature.

government.network.name: Network
government.network.definition: A set of connected arcs and nodes that may be associated with infrastructure, assets, locations, routes, and other business objects.

government.network_arc.name: Network Arc
government.network_arc.definition: A connection or association between nodes in a network.

government.network_node.name: Network Node
government.network_node.definition: A connection point in a network.

government.operation.name: Operation
government.operation.definition: An orchestration of work to achieve a specific objective constrained by time and location, which may include, for example, transportation center, monitoring station, law enforcement, or administrative shift cycles across government.

government.order.name: Order
government.order.definition: An instruction, by one party to another, to buy, sell, exchange, provide, or deliver goods or services.

government.order_item.name: Order Item
government.order_item.definition: An order element that refers to a specific good or service.

government.partner.name: Partner
government.partner.definition: A legal entity that has, plans to have, or has had some degree of involvement with the organization.

government.plan.name: Plan
government.plan.definition: An organized, sequenced set of steps or instructions, which may include milestones, intended to achieve a result when completed.

government.policy.name: Policy
government.policy.definition: A set of rules, procedures, regulations, and principles, or, a codified proposed intent.

government.public_sector_entity.name: Public Sector Entity
government.public_sector_entity.definition: A governmental body or collection of governmental bodies.

government.research.name: Research
government.research.definition: A systematic investigation into materials and sources intended to establish facts and produce insights.

government.route.name: Route
government.route.definition: A way or course taken in getting from a starting point to a destination, which may include stops along the way.

government.schedule_element.name: Schedule Element
government.schedule_element.definition: A line item that aligns time and one or more other objects, including work item, human resource, payment, event, or location.

government.standard.name: Standard
government.standard.definition: A convention, specification, or measurement, confirmed by a recognized governance body.

government.strategy.name: Strategy
government.strategy.definition: An integrated and aligned association of visions, goals, objectives, and courses of action that provides direction and guides activity.

government.course_of_action.name: Course of Action
government.course_of_action.definition: A set of activities to be taken to achieve an objective.

government.goal.name: Goal
government.goal.definition: An end toward which effort is or should be directed.

government.objective.name: Objective
government.objective.definition: A quantitative, measurable result that contributes to the realization of a goal.

government.vision.name: Vision
government.vision.definition: An imagined future state of being.

government.submission.name: Submission
government.submission.definition: A container that is used to exchange one or more requests, inquiries, messages, notifications, content, or other objects between parties.

government.time.name: Time
government.time.definition: A point or duration in the past, present, or future.

government.training_course.name: Training Course
government.training_course.definition: A structured theoretical or practical subject matter in a consumable format, associated with a curriculum, workshop, or seminar.

government.trip.name: Trip
government.trip.definition: A journey between a starting point location and one or more targeted locations until a final destination is reached.

government.vote.name: Vote
government.vote.definition: A formal indication of choice such as for a candidate election, referendum, or proposition.

government.work_item.name: Work Item
government.work_item.definition: A defined, well-bounded task that may be assigned to a stakeholder or corresponding asset.

government.work_queue.name: Work Queue
government.work_queue.definition: A container to hold, sequence, filter, structure, and present a set of work items.

finance.brand.name: Brand
finance.brand.definition: A name, symbol, or design that identifies and differentiates products, offerings, or organizational identities.

finance.business_entity.name: Business Entity
finance.business_entity.definition: A legal body or bodies that comprises or comprise a single organization.

finance.campaign.name: Campaign
finance.campaign.definition: An outreach activity that targets a specific population, for example, customers, human resources, partners, and patients, to achieve a certain goal, such as marketing awareness, hiring activities, and health awareness.

finance.initiative.name: Initiative
finance.initiative.definition: A coordinated collection of temporary endeavors undertaken to create a unique outcome.

finance.intellectual_property_rights.name: Intellectual Property Rights
finance.intellectual_property_rights.definition: Legal protections, such as patents, trademarks, and copyrights.

finance.market.name: Market
finance.market.definition: Individuals, populations of individuals, or organizations constituting the demand for existing or future products and services.

finance.message.name: Message
finance.message.definition: A verbal, written, recorded, or digitally-represented communication, including missives, notifications, alerts, and other internally or externally targeted communication about the organization's mission, products, plans, activities, and other focal points.

finance.plan.name: Plan
finance.plan.definition: A set of activities to achieve a result.

finance.policy.name: Policy
finance.policy.definition: A course or principle of action adopted or proposed by an organization.

finance.research.name: Research
finance.research.definition: A systematic investigation into materials and sources.

finance.strategy.name: Strategy
finance.strategy.definition: An integrated pattern and perspective that aligns an organization’s goals, objectives, and action sequences into a cohesive whole.

finance.goal.name: Goal
finance.goal.definition: An end toward which effort is or should be directed.

finance.objective.name: Objective
finance.objective.definition: A quantitative, measurable result that defines strategy.

finance.action_item.name: Action Item
finance.action_item.definition: A specific course to be taken to achieve an objective.

finance.vision.name: Vision
finance.vision.definition: An Imagined future state of being.

finance.agreement.name: Agreement
finance.agreement.definition: A set of legally binding rights and obligations between two or more legal entities.

finance.agreement_term.name: Agreement Term
finance.agreement_term.definition: A legally enforceable condition set forth within the bounds of an agreement.

finance.channel.name: Channel
finance.channel.definition: A digital, analog, or physical conduit through which products, related services, or communications are delivered or received, including the Internet, phone, delivery service, satellite, radio, or physical means.

finance.customer.name: Customer
finance.customer.definition: A legal entity that has, plans to have, or has had an agreement with the organization, or is a recipient or beneficiary of the organization's products or services.

finance.partner.name: Partner
finance.partner.definition: A legal entity that has, plans to have, or has had an agreement with the organization with the intent to exchange value in the provisioning of assets, services, products, or other means of assistance in the course of doing business.

finance.product.name: Product
finance.product.definition: A named combination of goods and services that can be offered to customers, in whole or in part.

finance.financial_instrument.name: Financial Instrument
finance.financial_instrument.definition: A tradable asset, such as stocks, bonds, bills of exchange, futures, options, evidence of ownership, and cash.

finance.order.name: Order
finance.order.definition: A request by one party to another to buy, sell, or exchange financial instruments or other goods or services.

finance.investment_portfolio.name: Investment Portfolio
finance.investment_portfolio.definition: A set of resources expected to increase in value or provide income.

finance.collateral.name: Collateral
finance.collateral.definition: Property or other asset that a customer offers as security to a borrowing or lending agreement.

finance.currency.name: Currency
finance.currency.definition: An agreed medium of value exchange.

finance.financial_account.name: Financial Account
finance.financial_account.definition: A named container of monetary value transactions that are typically organized into assets, liabilities, income, expense, equity, and other related categories.

finance.financial_forecast.name: Financial Forecast
finance.financial_forecast.definition: A prediction of a future financial aspect of the organization.

finance.financial_transaction.name: Financial Transaction
finance.financial_transaction.definition: An instance of a monetary amount movement or related exchange across businesses, agreements, or financial accounts.

finance.monetary_amount.name: Monetary Amount
finance.monetary_amount.definition: A representation of value as expressed in a given currency.

finance.payment.name: Payment
finance.payment.definition: An obligation to remit or receive a monetary amount between an organization and a customer, partner, or other external party.

finance.tax.name: Tax
finance.tax.definition: A compulsory contribution of monetary value to governing bodies.

finance.competency.name: Competency
finance.competency.definition: The skills and knowledge necessary to do something.

finance.meeting.name: Meeting
finance.meeting.definition: A gathering of two or more persons at a determinable time and place, including physical and virtual engagements, conferences, or related gatherings.

finance.facility.name: Facility
finance.facility.definition: A physical structure at a given place where business is conducted.

finance.human_resource.name: Human Resource
finance.human_resource.definition: An individual who has, plans to have, or has had a legal agreement with the organization, which includes compensation and other benefits, on a temporary or permanent basis.

finance.incident.name: Incident
finance.incident.definition: An occurrence that is unpleasant, unusual, unexpected, untoward, or unintended.

finance.inquiry.name: Inquiry
finance.inquiry.definition: A question, request, feedback, or comment that may exist inside or outside of the business, which can be received, identified, harvested, disseminated, classified, and tracked.

finance.job.name: Job
finance.job.definition: A named category of accountabilities, whether remunerative or non-remunerative, associated with an assigned, specific, and accountable business duty, role, or function that can be executed by a human or non-human resource.

finance.language.name: Language
finance.language.definition: A method of communication or dialect variant consisting of units of representation or meaning, such as numbers, words, symbols, sounds, or other physical manifestations and gestures, presented in a structured way.

finance.legal_proceeding.name: Legal Proceeding
finance.legal_proceeding.definition: An activity invoking the power of a tribunal to enforce a law.

finance.content.name: Content
finance.content.definition: A creative work, such as is manifested in audio/visual, still image, textual, experiential, mixed-media, or other forms.

finance.training_course.name: Training Course
finance.training_course.definition: The structured theoretical or practical subject matter in a consumable format, associated with a curriculum, workshop, or seminar.

finance.work.name: Work
finance.work.definition: Tasks, inbound requests, schedules, events, and related decisions.

finance.work_item.name: Work Item
finance.work_item.definition: A defined, well-bounded task that may be assigned to a stakeholder or corresponding asset.

finance.work_queue.name: Work Queue
finance.work_queue.definition: A container to hold, sequence, filter, structure, and present a set of work items.

finance.decision.name: Decision
finance.decision.definition: A conclusion or resolution reached after considering alternative options.

finance.submission.name: Submission
finance.submission.definition: Inbound requests, communications, and other content.

finance.schedule.name: Schedule
finance.schedule.definition: An aggregation of times, dates, and milestones.

finance.time.name: Time
finance.time.definition: A point or duration in the past, present, or future.
